# Common Viva Questions

## Q1. Why did you choose FastAPI?

Answer

FastAPI provides asynchronous request handling, automatic OpenAPI documentation, type validation, and integrates naturally with Python AI libraries.

---

## Q2. Why not use Node.js for the backend?

Answer

The project relies heavily on AI processing and data analysis. Python offers a richer ecosystem for machine learning, document parsing, and AI orchestration.

---

## Q3. Why PostgreSQL instead of MongoDB?

Answer

The application has strong relationships between users, repositories, reports, and recruiter data. PostgreSQL provides ACID compliance, robust indexing, and JSON support for semi-structured data.

---

## Q4. Why Redis?

Answer

Redis is used for caching, session management, and background job queues, improving responsiveness and reducing repeated API calls.

---

## Q5. Why Celery?

Answer

Repository analysis and AI generation are time-consuming. Celery allows these tasks to run asynchronously without blocking user requests.

---

## Q6. Why Docker?

Answer

Docker ensures consistent environments across development, testing, and production, simplifying deployment.

---

## Q7. What makes your project different?

Answer

Most GitHub tools report activity metrics. Our platform analyzes engineering practices, validates skills using repository evidence, generates career recommendations, and supports recruiter workflows in one integrated system.

---

## Q8. How do you reduce AI hallucinations?

Answer

We use a Rules Engine and Analytics Engine to extract deterministic evidence first. The AI receives structured facts rather than raw repositories, making outputs more reliable and explainable.

---

## Q9. How does the recruiter module rank candidates?

Answer

It combines résumé information, GitHub evidence, engineering scores, and job requirements to generate transparent rankings rather than relying only on keyword matching.

---

## Q10. How is user data protected?

Answer

OAuth authentication, JWT-based authorization, HTTPS, encrypted secrets, input validation, rate limiting, and secure cloud storage are used throughout the platform.

